<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="62" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1644,1873]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,279,1644,1670]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A genus in 
<taxonomicName box="[423,584,1644,1670]" class="Pauropoda" family="Pauropodidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetramerocerata" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pauropodidae</taxonomicName>
characterized by anterior margin of sternal antennal branch shorter than posterior margin, antennal globulus 
<emphasis box="[579,594,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">g</emphasis>
short-stalked, pygidial sternum with setae 
<emphasis box="[1103,1117,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">b</emphasis>
<number box="[1118,1126,1700,1714]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
+ 
<emphasis box="[1142,1157,1684,1709]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">b</emphasis>
<number box="[1157,1165,1700,1714]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="3.0">3</number>
, legs 
<number box="[1237,1252,1684,1710]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="1.0">1</number>
and 
<number box="[1310,1354,1684,1710]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="8.0" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="7.0">7–9</number>
<number box="[1363,1377,1684,1710]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="5.0">5</number>
-segmented, interposed pairs 
<number box="[445,458,1727,1753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="6.0">6</number>
-segmented and adults with at most 
<number box="[881,896,1727,1753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="9.0">9</number>
pair of legs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1644,1873]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,447,1767,1793]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Derivation of name.</emphasis>
From Latin juxta = near, close to (
<taxonomicName box="[855,1014,1767,1792]" class="Pauropoda" family="Pauropodidae" genus="Allopauropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetramerocerata" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[855,1014,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Allopauropus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1071,1184,1767,1792]" class="Pauropoda" family="Pauropodidae" genus="Pauropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetramerocerata" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1071,1184,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Pauropus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,366,1807,1833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Type-species:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Remy, 1950" authorityName="Remy" authorityYear="1950" box="[373,1015,1807,1833]" class="Pauropoda" family="Pauropodidae" genus="Scleropauropus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Tetramerocerata" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crinitus" subGenus="Scleropauropus">
<emphasis box="[373,556,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Scleropauropus</emphasis>
(
<emphasis box="[574,757,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">Scleropauropus</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis box="[774,864,1807,1832]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="62">crinitus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Remy" box="[871,1015,1807,1833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="68" refString="Remy, P. A. (1950) Pauropodes argentins recoltes par M. Julio A. Rosas Costa dans le territoire de Misiones. Bulletin du Museum national d´Histoire naturelle, Paris, (2) 22 (2), 245 - 249." type="journal article" year="1950">
Remy, 
<number box="[954,1015,1807,1833]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="1950.0">1950</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, by present designation. The following 
<number box="[373,388,1847,1873]" pageId="3" pageNumber="62" value="9.0">9</number>
species have to be moved here.
</paragraph>
